  "original_title": "'\u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc7 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1 - \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc7 \u0b9a\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd' \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bb2\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Handing over of the report of the Presidential Secretariat to the President on 'One Country - One Law'",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "The report of the Presidential Secretariat on 'One Nation - One Law' was handed over to President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa on Wednesday 29th by the Chairman of the Secretariat Galagoda Atte Gnanasara Thera.",
        "The Presidential Task Force was established on October 26, 2021 and November 6, 2021 to issue proposals for the creation of a unique ideological framework for Sri Lanka after examining the views of various parties and suggestions on the implementation of the concept of 'One Nation - One Law' in Sri Lanka.",
        "Prof. Shanthi Nandana Wijesinghe, Senior Lecturer Weerawardhanalake Sumedha Manjula, Dr. NG Sujeewa Panditharatne, Attorney-at-Law Iresh Seneviratne, Attorney-at-Law WPJMR Sanjaya Bandara Marambe, R.A. Erantha Kumara Navaratne, Bani Wewala, Moulavi M. A.S. Mohamed (Bari), Yogeshwari Pargunaraja and Iyampillai Dayanandaraja are the other members of the task force. Jivanthi Senanayake, Senior Assistant Secretary to the President, served as Secretary of the Task Force.",
        "The report is made up of 8 chapters with 43 recommendations and 2 appendices, including witnesses from more than 1,200 people from all over the country, including professionals, NGOs, religious groups, various ethnic groups, the university community and legal professionals. It is noteworthy that the President has directed that this report be submitted to the Cabinet and Parliament."
      ],
